           // Polyfill for IE11\n            Math.tanh = Math.tanh || function(x){\n                var a = Math.exp(+x), b = Math.exp(-x);\n                return a == Infinity ? 1 : (b == Infinity ? -1 : (a - b) / (a + b));\n            }\n\n            function degreesToRadians(deg) {\n              return deg * (Math.PI / 180);\n            }\n\n            function radiansToDegrees(rad) {\n              return rad / (Math.PI / 180);\n            }\n\n            function getBoundsAndZoomLevel(northLat, southLat, westLng, eastLng, spaceHeight, spaceWidth) {\n                var WORLD_DIM = { height: 256, width: 256 };\n                var ZOOM_MAX = 19;\n\n                function latRad(lat) {\n                    var sin = Math.sin(degreesToRadians(lat));\n                    var radX2 = Math.log((1 + sin) / (1 - sin)) / 2;\n                    return Math.max(Math.min(radX2, Math.PI), -Math.PI) / 2;\n                }\n\n                function fracToZoom(mapPx, worldPx, fraction) {\n                    var v = Math.log(mapPx / worldPx / fraction) / Math.LN2;\n                    // Adjust for floating error on exact fit\n                    return Math.floor(v + 0.00001);\n                }\n\n                function zoomToFrac(mapPx, worldPx, zoom) {\n                    return (mapPx / worldPx) / Math.exp(zoom * Math.LN2);\n                }\n\n                // ====================================================================\n                // Calculate the zoom level to fit these bounds into the given viewport\n                // ====================================================================\n\n                // Sphere math to turn lat and long into degrees out of 360\n                var latRadNorth = latRad(northLat);\n                var latRadSouth = latRad(southLat);\n                var latRadDiff = latRadNorth - latRadSouth;\n                var latFraction = latRadDiff / Math.PI;\n\n                var lngDiff = eastLng - westLng;\n                var lngFraction = ((!(lngDiff >= 0)) ? (lngDiff + 360) : lngDiff) / 360;\n\n                var latZoom = fracToZoom(spaceHeight, WORLD_DIM.height, latFraction);\n                var lngZoom = fracToZoom(spaceWidth, WORLD_DIM.width, lngFraction);\n\n                var finalZoom = Math.min(latZoom, lngZoom, ZOOM_MAX);\n\n                // ========================================================\n                // Calculate the viewport-exact bounds for this zoom level\n                // ========================================================\n\n                var fittedLngFraction = zoomToFrac(spaceWidth, WORLD_DIM.width, finalZoom);\n                var lngDegreeCenter = (eastLng + westLng) / 2;\n                var fittedLngDiff = lngDiff * (fittedLngFraction / lngFraction)\n                var fittedWestLng = lngDegreeCenter - (fittedLngDiff / 2);\n                var fittedEastLng = lngDegreeCenter + (fittedLngDiff / 2);\n\n                var fittedLatRadFraction = zoomToFrac(spaceHeight, WORLD_DIM.height, finalZoom);\n                var latRadCenter = (latRadNorth + latRadSouth) / 2;\n                var fittedLatRadDiff = latRadDiff * (fittedLatRadFraction / latFraction);\n                var fittedNorthLat = radiansToDegrees(Math.asin(Math.tanh(2 * (latRadCenter + (fittedLatRadDiff/2)))));\n                var fittedSouthLat = radiansToDegrees(Math.asin(Math.tanh(2 * (latRadCenter - (fittedLatRadDiff/2)))));\n\n                return {\n                    zoom: finalZoom,\n                    bounds: {\n                        northLat: fittedNorthLat,\n                        southLat: fittedSouthLat,\n                        eastLng: fittedEastLng,\n                        westLng: fittedWestLng,\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            /*\n                This must be kept synchronized with these vars in https://gitlab.zgtools.net/zillow/searchxp/static-search-page/-/blob/master/src/search-app/less/constants.less\n                    @wideSingleColumnMinWidth\n                    @wideDoubleColumnMinWidth\n                    @searchListSingleColumnWidth_DoubleColTest\n                    @searchListDoubleColumnWidth_DoubleColTest\n            */\n            function getListCardColumnWidth() {\n                if (window.innerWidth >= 1280) {\n                    return 750;\n                } else if (window.innerWidth >= 1007) {\n                    return 375;\n                } else {\n                    return 0;\n                }\n            }\n\n            var northLat = 42.36038318627354;\n            var southLat = 42.309624995950585;\n            var westLng = -71.17123603820801;\n            var eastLng = -71.06823921203613;\n\n            var Z_HEADER_HEIGHT = 80;\n            var SRP_HEADER_HEIGHT = 55;\n\n            // Only prefetch when the window is wide enough to display a map and list view\n            if (window.innerWidth >= 1007){\n                var boundsAndZoom = getBoundsAndZoomLevel(northLat, southLat, westLng, eastLng, window.innerHeight - SRP_HEADER_HEIGHT - Z_HEADER_HEIGHT, window.innerWidth - getListCardColumnWidth());\n                window.boundsAndZoom = boundsAndZoom;\n                // Use a placeholder image one zoom level out, since we are stretching the image out 2x, which has the effect of zooming in.\n                window.selectedPrefetch = window.mapPlaceholders[boundsAndZoom.zoom-1];\n\n                // Kick off a prefetch since the image won\'t be actually consumed till SSP initial render\n                document.querySelector("#mapPrefetch").href = window.selectedPrefetch;\n            }\n
